.TH "pci_rebar_get_possible_sizes" 9 "pci_rebar_get_possible_sizes" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_rebar_get_possible_sizes \- get possible sizes for BAR
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" pci_rebar_get_possible_sizes
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "int bar "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device
.IP "bar" 12
BAR to query
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Get the possible sizes of a resizable BAR as bitmask defined in the spec
(bit 0=1MB, bit 19=512GB). Returns 0 if BAR isn't resizable.
